					<description><![CDATA[<p>Watch the views rack up with these YouTube SEO tips and other ideas so more people find your videos.</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/youtube-seo">YouTube SEO 101: How to Get Found on YouTube</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.wordstream.com">WordStream</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>If you‚Äôre looking to grow your brand‚Äôs reach with more creative content strategies, you‚Äôre probably already considering YouTube. And it‚Äôs worth a try. In fact, the Content Marketing Institute found that YouTube is an effective marketing channel for <a href="https://contentmarketinginstitute.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/B2C_2023_Research_Final.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener">86%</a> of B2C brands, and for <a href="https://contentmarketinginstitute.com/articles/b2b-content-marketing-trends-research/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">22%</a> of B2B brands, YouTube is their top-performing channel.</p>
<p>But when you‚Äôre spending the time‚Äîand, in some cases, the budget‚Äîto create compelling video content, you want to get the most out of it. That‚Äôs why establishing your YouTube SEO strategy early and checking in often is helpful.</p>
<p>Here‚Äôs how to get started.</p>
<h3>Contents</h3>
<ul>
<li><a href="#youtube-seo-tips">YouTube SEO tips and basics</a></li>
<li><a href="#how-to-get-found-on-youtube">More ways to get found on YouTube</a></li>
<li><a href="#get-started-with-youtube-seo">Get started</a></li>
</ul>
<div id="youtube-seo-tips"></div>
<h2>YouTube SEO tips to get your content in front of more viewers</h2>
<p>YouTube is a platform for video content, but it‚Äôs important to remember it‚Äôs also a search engine. And some might even argue (like in <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2023/02/03/opinion/youtube-beats-google.html">The New York Times</a>) that it‚Äôs a better one than Google. Here are tips for approaching your YouTube content creation and promotion with SEO in mind:</p>
<h3>1. Do keyword research</h3>
<p>Whether it‚Äôs the foundation of your <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/07/13/content-marketing-strategy">content strategy</a> or a step in your brainstorming, keyword research belongs in your content ideation process. This is true for blog posts and guides that you want to rank on the Google SERP. It‚Äôs also true for YouTube. These videos could appear on the Google SERP, and you want them to show up on YouTube‚Äôs own search results page. Because, after all, YouTube is a search engine.</p>
<p>So when you‚Äôre creating YouTube videos, check for keyword opportunities. You can take a look at trending videos on your own account‚Äôs homepage to start. Common <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/best-seo-tools">SEO tools</a> like Semrush and Ahrefs have the option to focus keyword research on YouTube. This will let you explore many of the same features‚Äîkeyword term matches, long-tail related keywords, and level of competition to rank.</p>
<p><a href="https://trends.google.com/trends/explore?gprop=youtube" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Trends</a> also has a drop-down option to select YouTube Search to explore trending topics. This is another option (especially if you don‚Äôt have a subscription to Ahrefs, Semrush, or a similar tool) to look into keyword opportunities. The features aren‚Äôt as extensive, but you can check out interest in a certain area and get some ideas for related keywords.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/youtube-seo-do-keyword-research.webp" alt="using google trends for youtube seo" width="886" height="539" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-84429" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/youtube-seo-do-keyword-research.webp 886w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/youtube-seo-do-keyword-research-480x292.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 886px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>Remember, you can also optimize retroactively. If you have a channel up and running, take a look at the video content on there and follow these steps to see if there‚Äôs an opportunity to target your title or description‚Äîwhich brings us to the next tip.</p>
<p><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f50e.png" alt="üîé" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> <strong>Need help finding the right keywords?</strong> Try our <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/keywords?cid=Web_Any_InContentTextLink_Keywords_KWTool">Free Keyword Tool</a>!</p>
<h3>2. Optimize your titles and descriptions</h3>
<p>Once you have your keywords, make sure that your video title and description are optimized for SEO. Here are a few tips:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Use your target keywords.</strong> Include your target keyword in your title, ideally at the beginning. And these should appear in your description, as well.</li>
<li><strong>Keep it short.</strong> The title should land between 50 and 60 characters, and your description between 125 and 200 characters.</li>
<li><strong>Be descriptive and specific. </strong>The titles and descriptions should match the content of the video‚Äîkeyword intent matters on YouTube, too.</li>
</ul>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/youtube-seo-optimize-titles.webp" alt="example of youtube results with optimized titles" width="887" height="544" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-84430" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/youtube-seo-optimize-titles.webp 887w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/youtube-seo-optimize-titles-480x294.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 887px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>The first organic result matches the search term exactly.¬†</em></p>
<h3>3. Add relevant tags</h3>
<p>Tags are keywords that you can add to your video‚Äôs metadata. YouTube isn‚Äôt clear on how effective tags are for reaching new viewers. The answer on <a href="https://support.google.com/youtube/answer/146402">YouTube Help</a> states that ‚Äúyou can add [tags] to your video to help viewers find your content,‚Äù and that they ultimately ‚Äúplay a minimal role in your video&#8217;s discovery.‚Äù</p>
<p>But when you‚Äôre uploading your video to YouTube, it takes just a few moments to add tags. So it‚Äôs worth adding these, whether or not the impact is ‚Äúminimal.‚Äù On the details section of the video upload screen, after you‚Äôve added your title and description, scroll down and click on the prompt to show more.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/youtube-seo-add-tags.webp" alt="add tags to videos for youtube seo" width="859" height="435" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-84431" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/youtube-seo-add-tags.webp 859w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/youtube-seo-add-tags-480x243.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 859px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>Once the tags section appears, write in a few words and phrases to describe the content of your video. For example, if you‚Äôre uploading a video on baking a cake, you might include: how to bake a cake, baking a birthday cake, pineapple upside down cake.</p>
<p>Pro tip: If it‚Äôs a tutorial for how to use your product or your service, make sure to include your brand name as a tag.</p>
<p><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f4da.png" alt="üìö" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" />¬†<strong>Free guide download</strong>¬†&gt;&gt;¬†<a href="https://marketing.wordstream.com/WSLIQContentDLWebsite36CallToActionPhrases.html?cid=Web_Any_InContentTextLink_36CallToActionPhrases_Download">The 36 Best Call to Action Phrases Ever (&amp; Why They Work)</a></p>
<h3>4. Select a category</h3>
<p>Below the section to add tags, you‚Äôll have the option to select a category for your YouTube video. It‚Äôs unclear whether a category impacts reach‚Äîsome threads on Reddit say it can improve or tank performance and others question whether it does anything. But like adding tags, selecting a category takes just a moment, so it‚Äôs worth adding to your routine. If it does increase your chances to rank, you don‚Äôt want to miss the opportunity.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/youtube-seo-choose-video-categories.webp" alt="add category to youtube video for youtube seo" width="860" height="437" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-84432" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/youtube-seo-choose-video-categories.webp 860w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/youtube-seo-choose-video-categories-480x244.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 860px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>Here are the options that you have to select a category on YouTube:</p>
<ul>
<li>Autos &amp; Vehicles</li>
<li>Comedy</li>
<li>Education</li>
<li>Entertainment</li>
<li>Film &amp; Animation</li>
<li>Gaming</li>
<li>How to &amp; Style</li>
<li>Music</li>
<li>News &amp; Politics</li>
<li>Nonprofits &amp; Activism</li>
<li>People &amp; Blogs</li>
<li>Pets &amp; Animals</li>
<li>Science &amp; Technology</li>
<li>Sports</li>
<li>Travel &amp; Events</li>
</ul>
<p>Because the impact is unclear, don‚Äôt spend too much time debating here. Take the two seconds to choose the best fit for your video, then move on to more important factors in your YouTube SEO.</p>
<h3>5. Customize your thumbnail</h3>
<p>YouTube will automatically select a still frame from your video as a thumbnail when you upload. You do not want to use this. Instead, you want to take the time to create your own. According to YouTube, <a href="https://support.google.com/youtube/answer/12340300?hl=en" target="_blank" rel="noopener">90%</a> of the best-performing videos have custom thumbnails. People want to click on a visually appealing video, and a fuzzy still frame isn‚Äôt going to cut it.</p>
<p>Customizing your <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/12/07/youtube-thumbnail">YouTube thumbnail</a> can be a project for a designer, or it can be straightforward editing in Canva or even Google Slides with a screengrab and a title overlay. Take a look at the thumbnails for the budgeting videos below. They‚Äôre all different, but they‚Äôre all fairly low-production in terms of design elements. Most are still images with titles, screenshots, or logos added.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/youtube-seo-customize-thumbnail.webp" alt="example of customized youtube thumbnails" width="680" height="600" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-84433" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/youtube-seo-customize-thumbnail.webp 680w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/youtube-seo-customize-thumbnail-480x424.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 680px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>When you‚Äôre creating your custom thumbnail for YouTube, keep these specs in mind:</p>
<ul>
<li>Minimum resolution of 1280&#215;720.</li>
<li>Minimum width of 640 pixels.</li>
<li>File types JPG, GIF, or PNG.</li>
<li>Maximum file size 2MB for videos or 10MB for podcasts.</li>
<li>Required 16:9 aspect ratio.</li>
</ul>
<p>And while you‚Äôre customizing, don‚Äôt forget to add your logo as a watermark in the thumbnail, too.</p>
<h3>6. Set up playlists</h3>
<p>YouTube allows you to create playlists of multiple videos. Once you have a few related videos on your YouTube channel, it‚Äôs setting one up.</p>
<p>By setting up a playlist of related videos, you can keep engaged viewers watching your content for longer. This could be multiple videos on a certain topic, like the garden creation or cake baking we talked about earlier. It could also be videos for a specific audience, like a collection of videos with marketing tips or SMBs or yoga classes designed for teachers.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/youtube-seo-make-playlists.webp" alt="example of youtube playlist" width="839" height="362" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-84434" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/youtube-seo-make-playlists.webp 839w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/youtube-seo-make-playlists-480x207.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 839px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zRDQqJEuRcw&amp;list=PLui6Eyny-UzwjVpXSAgjOh8FPkpuwImex" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Source</em></a></p>
<h3>7. Double-check your file name</h3>
<p>I am guilty of downloading files and never adjusting the name. This is frustrating at the moment when I have 16 files named &#8220;screenshot&#8221; on my desktop. It‚Äôs also more than a missed organizational opportunity.</p>
<p>When it comes to your YouTube videos, take the time to rename the files with your keyword, or even your full title that might include ‚Äúhow to.‚Äù This is another opportunity to signal the content of the video to YouTube‚Äôs search engine in the video‚Äôs metadata.</p>
<h3>8. Review analytics and adjust your strategy</h3>
<p>Your YouTube SEO strategy will include a lot of front-end optimization to give your videos the best chance of reaching your audience. But it‚Äôs important to check in on performance.</p>
<p>From the sidebar of your YouTube Studio page, head to the Analytics section.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/youtube-seo-use-analytics.webp" alt="analytics section in youtube studio" width="226" height="542" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-84435" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/youtube-seo-use-analytics.webp 226w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/youtube-seo-use-analytics-125x300.webp 125w" sizes="(max-width: 226px) 100vw, 226px" /></p>
<p>Here, you‚Äôll see overall views, watch time, and channel subscribers. You can also dig into the performance of specific videos and details of your audience, including a breakdown of new and returning viewers. This will help you create new content, or even find ways to optimize existing content with new keywords, based on your audience‚Äôs interest. Plus, it‚Äôs a good way to see what isn‚Äôt working and save your time.</p>
<p>After all, YouTube has <a href="https://www.globalmediainsight.com/blog/youtube-users-statistics/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">2.7 billion users</a>. And these users spend an average of <a href="https://www.oberlo.com/statistics/average-time-spent-on-youtube" target="_blank" rel="noopener">48 minutes each day</a> interacting with content. Your audience is online, so it‚Äôs a matter of creating the content that they‚Äôre interested in viewing and getting that content in front of them.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/time-spent-on-youtube.webp" alt="chart showing time spent on youtube" width="874" height="480" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-84436" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/time-spent-on-youtube.webp 874w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/time-spent-on-youtube-480x264.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 874px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>YouTube SEO can help serve your video content to more interested viewers on YouTube and on the Google SERP, so it‚Äôs worth taking the extra time. But it isn‚Äôt the only way to get found on YouTube, so we have a few more tactics to grow your YouTube channel.</p>
<p><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f6d1.png" alt="üõë" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> <strong>Worried you&#8217;re wasting spend in Google Ads?</strong> Find out with a free, instant audit &gt;&gt; <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/google-adwords?cid=Web_Any_InContentTextLink_PPC_AWGrader_AWGrader">Google Ads Performance Grader</a></p>
<div id="how-to-get-found-on-youtube"></div>
<h2>More ways to get found on YouTube</h2>
<p>SEO is an important lever to improve your and get in front of more people on YouTube. But it isn‚Äôt the only way to get your channel and your video content out there. Here are a few more quick tips to try and increase your views.</p>
<h3>9. Create a channel trailer</h3>
<p>This is one of my favorite tips because I wish there were more YouTube channel trailers. These brief videos can:</p>
<ul>
<li>Introduce your audience to you and your brand.</li>
<li>Provide an overview of the type of content that you publish.</li>
<li>Preview the style of your YouTube videos.</li>
</ul>
<p>This last one is particularly helpful. If your content <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/2024-seo-strategies">strategy</a> leans heavily to posting videos of podcast interviews or how to series or confessional, chatty USG content, this is good to know upfront.</p>
<p>Plus, you don‚Äôt have to create much net-new content for this, as featuring highlights from your existing content is key. If you‚Äôre looking for more tips on putting this together, check out this guide to creating a <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/06/28/youtube-channel-trailer">YouTube channel trailer</a>.</p>
<h3>10. Share across other channels</h3>
<p><a href="https://www.wordstream.com/seo">SEO</a> is an excellent lever for reaching new audiences on YouTube. But if your business has followers on other platforms, there‚Äôs a good chance at least some of them are already using YouTube. They need to know about your content, there.</p>
<p>So <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/how-to-promote-your-youtube-channel">promote your YouTube content</a> in your other marketing channels. Embed relevant YouTube videos in your blog posts. If you have a <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/02/25/email-newsletter-ideas">newsletter</a>, you can add a section featuring your YouTube channel and include links to new videos in follow-up communications. If you have a following on LinkedIn or Instagram, post about your YouTube videos and include <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2014/10/09/call-to-action">CTAs</a> to subscribe to your channel there.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/promote-youtube-videos-on-social.webp" alt="example of youtube video promoted on social media" width="335" height="575" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-84437" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/promote-youtube-videos-on-social.webp 335w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/promote-youtube-videos-on-social-175x300.webp 175w" sizes="(max-width: 335px) 100vw, 335px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>YouTuber Zoe Sugg promotes her videos on her Instagram Stories.</em></p>
<p><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/260e.png" alt="‚òé" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> <strong>Free guide download</strong>¬†&gt;&gt;¬†<a href="https://marketing.wordstream.com/WSLIQContentDLWebsite36CallToActionPhrases.html?cid=Web_Any_InContentTextLink_36CallToActionPhrases_Download">The 42 Best Call to Action Phrases Ever (&amp; Why They Work)</a></p>
<h3>11. Develop a series</h3>
<p>Regular content is an excellent way to keep your regular viewers tuning in and attracting a new audience. Your series could be a long-standing series, like product release round-ups or a video recording of your brand‚Äôs podcast.</p>
<p>But you can also experiment with a time box. For instance, try out some <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/july-content-ideas">summer-themed content</a> related to your brand, whether it‚Äôs a series of lawn care videos throughout June or a weekly rating of new ice cream shops in your area. (Who isn‚Äôt searching for the best cookie dough scoop around?)</p>
<p>And be sure to add the series videos to a playlist for your viewers to navigate easily, even after it‚Äôs complete.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/youtube-seo-develop-series.webp" alt="example of youtube video series" width="839" height="356" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-84438" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/youtube-seo-develop-series.webp 839w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/youtube-seo-develop-series-480x204.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 839px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.youtube.com/@yogawithadriene/playlists" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Yoga With Adriene</em></a><em> has been running 30 days of yoga series for years‚Äîand now has tons of playlists for new viewers.</em></p>
<h3>12. Get started with YouTube Shorts</h3>
<p>YouTube‚Äôs short-form video content, aptly titled <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/how-to-make-youtube-shorts/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">YouTube Shorts</a>, has a huge audience. In the US alone, there were <a href="https://www.statista.com/statistics/1459687/us-youtube-shorts-us-viewers/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">152 million monthly users</a> engaging with YouTube Shorts on the platform. And this user base is expected to keep growing.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/number-of-youtube-shorts.webp" alt="chart showing growing number of youtube shorts" width="894" height="599" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-84440" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/number-of-youtube-shorts.webp 894w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/number-of-youtube-shorts-480x322.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 894px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.statista.com/statistics/1459687/us-youtube-shorts-us-viewers/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Source</em></a></p>
<p><a href="https://localiq.com/blog/how-to-make-youtube-shorts/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">YouTube Shorts</a> are vertically oriented for better viewing (and swiping through) on a smartphone. These videos range in length, but they‚Äôre limited to 60 seconds. Your YouTube shorts will be featured on your channel page, and they‚Äôll also be served in YouTube‚Äôs search engine in addition to the main video content.</p>
<p>YouTube Shorts are also quickly becoming a major advertising opportunity. Last year, ad buyers reported that <a href="https://www.emarketer.com/content/meta-tiktok-youtube-prepare-face-off-2023-newfronts">43% </a>of their clients were advertising on YouTube Shorts, alongside TikTok and Instagram Reels. Something to keep in mind if you‚Äôre running ads on YouTube, too, which brings us to our final tip here.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/youtube-shorts-example.webp" alt="example of youtube shorts" width="426" height="600" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-84439" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/youtube-shorts-example.webp 426w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/youtube-shorts-example-213x300.webp 213w" sizes="(max-width: 426px) 100vw, 426px" /></p>
<h3>13. Try paid promotion</h3>
<p>The best way to ensure that your video content gets in front of your desired audience on YouTube is to run ads. <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2017/02/23/youtube-advertising-tips">YouTube&#8217;s advertising options</a> include brief bumper ads, skippable and non-skippable instream, infeed ads, and more. When it comes to content for your ad, you‚Äôll want a clear CTA and you can even use snippets of existing videos.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/youtube-advertising-cost.webp" alt="graphic showing average youtube advertising cost" width="887" height="581" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-84441" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/youtube-advertising-cost.webp 887w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/youtube-advertising-cost-480x314.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 887px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>For more tips for trialing paid promotion to grow your audience, check out this guide to <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/06/03/how-to-advertise-on-youtube">advertising on YouTube</a>.</p>
<div id="get-started-with-youtube-seo"></div>
<h2>Go get more views with better YouTube SEO</h2>
<p>YouTube is a huge marketing opportunity for internet personalities, small business brands, and major corporations. The key to success is finding your audience on the platform, and a strong YouTube SEO strategy can help.</p>
<p>Here‚Äôs an overview of our YouTube SEO essentials, plus our bonus tips to get found:</p>
<ol>
<li>Do keyword research</li>
<li>Optimize your titles and descriptions</li>
<li>Add relevant tags</li>
<li>Select a category</li>
<li>Customize your thumbnail</li>
<li>Set up playlists</li>
<li>Double-check your file name</li>
<li>Review analytics</li>
<li>Create a YouTube channel trailer</li>
<li>Share across other marketing channels</li>
<li>Develop a series</li>
<li>Get started with YouTube Shorts</li>
<li>Try paid promotion</li>
</ol>
<p>Now, go get more views on YouTube!</p>
