										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>By now, we‚Äôre all knee-deep in planning for 2024‚Äîidentifying new campaigns to test, putting together budgets, setting marketing goals, and defining the channels we‚Äôll focus on. Whether you have a robust video marketing strategy or you‚Äôre debating on buying your first iPhone tripod, one thing‚Äôs clear: <strong>Your business will benefit from more video content this year.</strong></p>
<p>There‚Äôs a reason video marketing is so effective for reaching people. When it‚Äôs done right, videos are easy to interact with, entertaining to consume, and quick to share. In fact, in a recent video marketing study, <a href="https://wyzowl.s3.eu-west-2.amazonaws.com/pdfs/Wyzowl-Video-Survey-2023.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener">51%</a> of respondents reported that they are more likely to share video content over social posts, blogs, or product pages.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/video-marketing-trends-sharing-content-chart.jpg" alt="video marketing trends - preferred shared content chart" width="936" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-79422 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/video-marketing-trends-sharing-content-chart.jpg 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/video-marketing-trends-sharing-content-chart-480x308.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>That‚Äôs great for building your brand and growing your audience. As long as you make the most of it. Cue video marketing trends. Following video marketing trends to inspire your business&#8217;s video strategy will increase your chances of securing views, engagement, and shares.</p>
<p>To start, we wanted to know what to expect in video marketing next year: the types of videos, the distribution methods, and the production tips. So we asked marketing leaders, video producers, and video editors what they think we‚Äôll see more of.</p>
<p>Let&#8217;s get into it!</p>
<h2><span>The top video marketing trends for 2024</span></h2>
<p>Here are the video marketing trends that the experts expect to see in 2024.</p>
<h3><span>1. </span><span>More use of AI tools and tricks</span></h3>
<p>This couldn‚Äôt be a list of trends for marketing next year without featuring AI. The advancements in <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ai-copywriting-tools">artificial intelligence</a> (AI), and generative AI in particular, have been all over the news this year. For example, Open AI launched the trained generative chatbot ChatGPT 3.5 at the end of 2022, and then an updated ChatGPT 4.0. There have been tons of other applications for this technology on the market and in the headlines this year, including resources for <span><a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/06/05/generative-ai-in-digital-marketing">generative AI in digital marketing</a></span>.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/video-marketing-trends-ai-google-trends.jpg" alt="video marketing trends - screenshot of ai search in google trends" width="783" height="476" class="aligncenter wp-image-79477 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/video-marketing-trends-ai-google-trends.jpg 783w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/video-marketing-trends-ai-google-trends-480x292.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 783px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Google Trends captures the huge increase in interest in AI over the last two years. </em></p>
<p>Danielle Warren, senior video editor at <span><a href="https://about.google/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google</a></span>, expects this to be a major trend in video marketing in 2024. ‚ÄúAI will of course continue to be a huge topic and trend going forward,‚Äù she said. ‚ÄúAs more and more AI-powered tools come onto the market, their significance in video marketing strategies will only grow. AI tools will increase productivity and help video teams ‚Äòdo more with less.‚Äô‚Äù</p>
<p>Additionally, AI video creation is a video marketing trend that&#8217;s already providing positive results. <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/ai-statistics/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">AI statistics</a> show that <a href="https://www.wyzowl.com/video-marketing-statistics/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">75%</a> of businesses are using AI to help them create or edit marketing videos and <a href="https://www.digitalmarketer.com/blog/ai-impacts-video-marketing/#:~:text=Let's%20start%20with%20some%20overall,using%20AI%20tools%20for%20work." target="_blank" rel="noopener">96%</a> of businesses have already seen a positive ROI from AI-powered video marketing.</p>
<p><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f5d3.png" alt="üóì" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> Get more marketing ideas, tips, and trends for this year in our free <a href="https://marketing.localiq.com/WSLIQContentDLWebsite2024MarketingCalendar.html?cid=Web_WS_InContent_Guide_2024MarketingCalendar_Download" target="_blank" rel="noopener">2024 marketing calendar</a>!</p>
<h3><span>2. </span><span>Fewer videos in SERP results (sort of)</span></h3>
<p><span>Earlier this year, Google <a href="https://www.searchenginejournal.com/google-reduces-video-thumbnails-in-serps/484589/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">announced</a> that it would significantly reduce the number of video thumbnails that appeared on the SERP. Specifically, Google said that it would stop featuring videos that weren‚Äôt the main content of the page.</span></p>
<p><span>This has already resulted in fewer videos on the SERP, and marketers are now planning for this in their <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/07/13/content-marketing-strategy">content strategies</a>. A video that‚Äôs not central to the page won‚Äôt rank‚Äîbut the main content will. </span></p>
<p><span>Here‚Äôs an example of a real-life query and the very helpful thumbnails that still appear from YouTube. Notice, though, that there weren‚Äôt any videos pulled from the comments on Quora‚Äôs SERP result.</span></p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/video-marketing-trends-example-serp-results.jpg" alt="video marketing trends - screenshot of current google serp" width="767" height="602" class="aligncenter wp-image-79478 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/video-marketing-trends-example-serp-results.jpg 767w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/video-marketing-trends-example-serp-results-480x377.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 767px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>What does this video marketing trend mean? Make sure your main videos are correctly featured and don‚Äôt expect to rank for peripheral video content. But still a good idea to prioritize your <span><a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2017/06/02/video-seo" target="_blank" rel="noopener">video SEO</a></span> next year.</p>
<p><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f4f9.png" alt="üìπ" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> Get more insight into your Google display and video campaign performance using our free<a href="https://www.wordstream.com/google-adwords?cid=Web_Any_InContentTextLink_PPC_AWGrader_AWGrader" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> Google Ads Grader</a>!</p>
<h3><span>3. Videos will be included in newsletter </span><span>and email creative</span></h3>
<p>Something that we saw a lot in 2023? Newsletters. According to reletter, there are more than <span><a href="https://reletter.com/home" target="_blank" rel="noopener">1.6 million newsletters</a></span> on Substack and LinkedIn alone.</p>
<p>This format allows for longer, more narrative communication with your audience. That‚Äôs a great opportunity for video content.</p>
<p>‚ÄúI&#8217;m looking forward to incorporating more videos into our email marketing strategy in 2024,‚Äù Natalie Cantave shared. Cantave runs marketing and partnerships for <span><a href="https://www.estateably.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Estateably</a></span>, and she co-founded the <span><a href="https://www.mktgwmn.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">MKTG WMN</a></span> community. ‚ÄúShort videos have helped our customers experience the newest product features which will hopefully drive adoption, keep them satisfied, and result in client retention.‚Äù</p>
<h3><span>4. Product videos will become more prevalent</span></h3>
<p>Allen Finn, who runs marketing at <span><a href="https://www.triplewhale.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Triple Whale</a></span>, is prioritizing product videos next year, and he thinks he‚Äôs one of many marketing leaders making this plan.</p>
<p>‚ÄúWe‚Äôre changing most of our documentation to video (versus traditional written help docs),‚Äù he said. ‚ÄúIt‚Äôs more digestible, less intimidating, and much more efficient to update, which is essential for a product that changes as often as ours.‚Äù</p>
<p>This change also means investing in video marketing content for your highest-value audiences: your customers or your most engaged prospects. ‚ÄúWe‚Äôre replacing illustrations with gifs and product videos across the website to show the product as it is versus as an abstraction to drive interest and conversion from high-intent visitors,‚Äù he explained.</p>
<p>Focusing on product videos and gifs next year is a no-brainer for software companies, but featuring your offering in motion is great for any business, especially direct-to-consumer.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/video-marketing-trend-banza-video-screenshot.jpg" alt="video marketing trends - example banza product video" width="757" height="497" class="aligncenter wp-image-79479 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/video-marketing-trend-banza-video-screenshot.jpg 757w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/video-marketing-trend-banza-video-screenshot-480x315.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 757px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>In case anyone thinks <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4D7YXCCgi-E" target="_blank" rel="noopener">gluten-free mac and cheese</a> looks any different.</em></p>
<p>And if you‚Äôre featuring a service‚Äî-whether it‚Äôs your dental office or lawn care‚Äî-then you have a great reason to get in front of the camera. This brings us to the next video marketing trend to watch for next year.</p>
<h3><span>5. </span><span>More real people on camera</span></h3>
<p>Rayna van Beuzekom, video editor and producer at <span><a href="https://www.commsor.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Commsor</a></span>, thinks we‚Äôre going to see more people on camera as brands focus on the biggest value of video: connection.</p>
<p>‚ÄúVideo is such a great tool to connect with audiences,‚Äù they said. ‚ÄúYou can take a seemingly distant product and humanize it through video. We&#8217;re going to see more and more people on camera, whether it&#8217;s sellers, marketers or executives.‚Äù</p>
<p>Notice the key similarity among the ‚Äúwho‚Äù options Rayna gave? Sellers, marketers, and executives are all members of your team. Real people don‚Äôt mean actors or influencers; it means your company‚Äôs employees and partners.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/video-marketing-trends-conversational-instagram-reel.jpg" alt="video marketing trends - conversational instagram video example" width="664" height="590" class="aligncenter wp-image-79474 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/video-marketing-trends-conversational-instagram-reel.jpg 664w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/video-marketing-trends-conversational-instagram-reel-480x427.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 664px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em><a href="https://www.instagram.com/p/Cz9NoMYxJQn/?hl=en" target="_blank" rel="noopener">A great example</a> of casual, conversational founder videos from Lo Bosworth, CEO of Lovewellness and Laguna Beach alum.</em></p>
<p>Founder &amp; CEO at <span><a href="https://www.startupbos.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Startup Boston</a></span> Stephanie Roulic thinks this trend will be especially prevalent for startups. ‚ÄúDuring the early stages of marketing your company, video marketing is so incredibly important because, more often than not, you have to rely on utilizing your founders&#8217; personality and story to sell early adapters on why they should take a chance on you.‚Äù</p>
<p>Early-stage companies and small businesses are in the same boat here. Next year, Stephanie expects more company founders to appear in social videos. She said this will ‚Äúhighlight not just the value of your product, but the team behind your product to help develop trust between you and early customers.‚Äù</p>
<p>By creating connections and building trust, video marketing can have real long-term impacts on brand affinity. We‚Äôre expecting to see plenty of real faces to help with that next year.</p>
<h3><span>6. S</span><span>hort-form video for social is here to stay</span></h3>
<p>As of October 2023, there are <span><a href="https://www.statista.com/statistics/617136/digital-population-worldwide/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">4.95 billion</a></span> social media users globally, which accounts for 94% of internet users. With that many people logging into social media, it‚Äôs a guarantee that your audience is reachable. It‚Äôs just a matter of finding them.</p>
<p>One of the most effective ways to grow your brand‚Äôs reach across is<a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/08/10/social-media-video-marketing" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> short-form video marketing content on social media</a>. That‚Äôs why it‚Äôs not going anywhere in 2024.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/video-marketing-trends-short-form-video.jpg" alt="video marketing trends - tiktok example" width="793" height="475" class="aligncenter wp-image-79476 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/video-marketing-trends-short-form-video.jpg 793w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/video-marketing-trends-short-form-video-480x288.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 793px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em><a href="https://www.tiktok.com/@netflix/video/7307409212160888110" target="_blank" rel="noopener">An example </a>of a short-form TikTok video. </em></p>
<p style="text-align: left;">‚ÄúAs a short-form video editor, I may be a little biased, but I&#8217;m genuinely enthusiastic about the ongoing growth of short-form content,‚Äù Warren said. ‚ÄúBetween Instagram reels, <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/youtube-shorts-ideas/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">YouTube Shorts</a>, TikTok, and everything in between, the appetite for short-form videos is only going to increase after growing exponentially over the next few years. Given the ever-shortening of attention spans, the ability to narrate your brand&#8217;s visual stories in a succinct and engaging manner is essential for success.‚Äù</p>
<h3><span>7. L</span><span>ong-form video content returns</span></h3>
<p>Short-form video is here to stay for another year‚Äîat least. But video marketing experts are also expecting a renewed focus on other kinds of video in 2024.</p>
<p>‚ÄúI&#8217;m hopeful for more long-form content in 2024,‚Äù said van Beuzekom. ‚ÄúThere&#8217;s more room for creativity vs. just trying to make something fast, like in short form.‚Äù</p>
<p>They point specifically to an increase in<a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/06/03/how-to-advertise-on-youtube" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> YouTube video marketing and advertising</a>. And this makes sense. <span><a href="https://wyzowl.s3.eu-west-2.amazonaws.com/pdfs/Wyzowl-Video-Survey-2023.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener">78%</a></span> of marketers identify YouTube as the most successful video <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/06/26/marketing-channels" target="_blank" rel="noopener">marketing channel</a>.</p>
<p>The platform offers vertical shorts for users to flip through similar to TikTok, but its mainstay is long-form videos. That means YouTube is a great place for your recorded podcasts, your explainer videos, even your event recaps‚Äîwhich leads us to the next trend.</p>
<h3><span>8. More videos will be made without sound</span></h3>
<p><span>Did you know that, in 2017, <a href="https://digiday.com/media/silent-world-facebook-video/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">85%</a></span> of Facebook videos were watched without sound? This video marketing trend is back, as many users are now consuming even more social video content without sound. In fact, users spend an average of <span><a href="https://www.statista.com/statistics/433871/daily-social-media-usage-worldwide/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">151 minutes each day</a></span> on social platforms interacting with content, including videos with and without sound.</p>
<p>There‚Äôs a lot of<a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/06/22/instagram-reels-ideas-for-businesses" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> Instagram Reels</a> watched in the office, in waiting rooms, in bed beside a partner‚Äîwithout sound. If this is how users are consuming content, it should be easy to understand why this video marketing trend is continuing to grow.</p>
<p>Now, there are more tools than ever to help make sure silent videos are effective with complete, accurate captions. Plus, AI tools will make this easier for marketing teams to do, even without video expertise. This leads to our final video marketing trend.</p>
<h3><span>9. Brands will focus on thrifty video marketing</span></h3>
<p>This past year has been a rough one for tech. With¬†<a href="https://techcrunch.com/2023/11/30/tech-layoffs-2023-list/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">over 220k</a> layoffs last year and the reduced <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/marketing-budget/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">marketing budgets</a> impacting the industry‚Äôs freelancers, thrift is going to be a video marketing trend in 2024.</p>
<p>Earlier, Finn pointed to efficiency as an additional benefit of switching to product videos instead of written documentation. Warren also specifically referenced doing more with less as ‚Äúanother trend that is expected to continue into 2024, especially as tech and media companies regain momentum following a challenging 2023.‚Äù</p>
<p>Luckily, the rise of AI editing and more easy-to-use <span><a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/06/13/video-ad-tools" target="_blank" rel="noopener">video ad tools </a></span>will help marketers create some clips even without a video background. Vimeo, for example, released the AI-powered caption generator as well as a transcript-based editor for easy cuts.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/video-marketing-trends-youtube.jpg" alt="video marketing trends - example ai youtube editing " width="699" height="466" class="aligncenter wp-image-79475 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/video-marketing-trends-youtube.jpg 699w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/video-marketing-trends-youtube-480x320.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 699px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=B704fR5y3-U" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Source</a></em></p>
<p>Of course, nothing beats an expert producer and an adequate budget. But in 2024, the most important thing is getting video marketing for your brand out in the world.</p>
<p><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f4a1.png" alt="üí°" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> Find more ways to incorporate AI in your video marketing and beyond with our free<a href="https://marketing.localiq.com/WSLIQContentDLWebsiteAIinMarketingGuide.html?cid=Web_Any_BlogInContent_PPC_AIMarketing_Download" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> AI in marketing</a> guide!</p>
<h2><span>Get started with these video marketing trends </span></h2>
<p>Remember, sometimes trends end up here to stay: Spotify Wrapped, all-white kitchens, doodles. Start experimenting with the video marketing trends above now, and your business&#8217;s <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/video-marketing-strategy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">video marketing strategy</a> will be ahead of the game. If you tried these video marketing trends but still want to bring your strategy to the next level, see how<a href="https://www.wordstream.com/marketing-services" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> our solutions</a> can help you make the most of your business&#8217;s videos.</p>
<p><strong>Here are the top 2024 video marketing trends:</strong></p>
<ol>
<li>More use of AI tools and tricks</li>
<li>Fewer videos on the SERP (sort of)</li>
<li>Videos will be included in newsletter and email creative</li>
<li>Product videos will become more prevalent</li>
<li>More real people on camera</li>
<li>Short-form video for social is here to stay</li>
<li>Long-form video content returns</li>
<li>More videos will be made without sound</li>
<li>Brands will focus on thrifty video marketing</li>
</ol>
