										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://media.sproutsocial.com/uploads/The-2023-State-of-Social-Media.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener">96%</a> of business leaders agree that companies that want to be successful must continue to invest in social media. So the question here isn‚Äôt really <em>if</em> you should have a strong social game but <em>which</em> platforms give you the most bang for your buck?</p>
<p>And that‚Äôs where the whole TikTok vs. YouTube debate stems from‚Äîboth platforms can help businesses connect with audiences, drive purchases, and build a sense of community through video.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/tiktok-vs-youtube.webp" alt="tiktok vs youtube logos" width="936" height="553" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-77151" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/tiktok-vs-youtube.webp 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/tiktok-vs-youtube-480x284.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>But what‚Äôs unique about both platforms is they‚Äôre also used as search engines by users. In fact, <a href="https://www.searchenginejournal.com/seo/meet-search-engines/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">YouTube is the second-largest search engine</a>. And for Gen Z, <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2022/09/16/technology/gen-z-tiktok-search-engine.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">TikTok is Google</a>.</p>
<p>Whether you create tailored content for these platforms to grow organically, partner with influencers, or run ads to drive sales, both YouTube and TikTok have a lot to offer.</p>
<h3>Table of contents</h3>
<ul>
<li><a href="#what-are-tiktok-and-youtube">What are TikTok and YouTube?</a></li>
